    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="173"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Draft Message From the <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d173fn1">Written in longhand by <persName corresp="#p_HHL1"
                            >Hopkins</persName>. For <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>’s message of October 30, 1943, to <persName
                            corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName> (prepared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName>), which may have been a revision of
                        this draft, see <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-30">October 30 (?),
                            1943</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">To <persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName>
                    </hi>
                </p>
                <p>Please tell <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> that my understanding
                    of my [blank] of October 24 [<hi rend="italic">26?</hi>]<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d173fn2">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_120">p.
                            120</ref>.</note> relative to disposition of Italian naval ships and
                    merchant ships is as follows quote</p>
                <p>One third of naval ships and one third of merchant ships captured from Italy will
                    be turned over to Russia for their use at the earliest possible moment[.] The
                    balance available for British and/or American use.</p>
                <pb facs="0220" n="128" xml:id="pg_128"/>
                <p>The final disposition of these ships however will be made by our three countries
                    at the peace conference and meanwhile Russia, Great Britain and ourselves will
                    have the unrestricted right to use this [<hi rend="italic">these</hi>] ships as
                    we think best to bring about the defeat of <persName corresp="#p_HA1"
                        >Hitler</persName>[.]</p>
                <p>I assumed we met the Russian request[.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
